title: Summary - Hurricane Tammy (AT5/AL202023)
author: nhcwebmaster@noaa.gov (NHC Webmaster)
summary:
...TAMMY STRENGTHENS OVER THE OPEN ATLANTIC... ...FORECAST TO BECOME A POWERFUL EXTRATROPICAL CYCLONE...
 As of 5:00 AM AST Wed Oct 25
 the center of Tammy was located near 25.6, -60.2
 with movement NE at 10 mph.
 The minimum central pressure was 969 mb
 with maximum sustained winds of about 100 mph.
